**Testing React components without Testing Library:**
- This project renders via `createRoot` + `act()` from `react-dom/client` / `react` вҖ” the same primitive React Testing Library wraps, but without the abstraction overhead
- `mouseover`/`mouseout` must be used instead of `mouseenter`/`mouseleave` because React 18 delegates these bubbling events to the root container. Non-bubbling `mouseenter` events dispatched on a child won't reach React's event handler on the root.
- The `data-breadcrumb-ancestor` attribute is a well-placed hook for testing вҖ” it lets tests distinguish clickable ancestors from the current (last) segment without fragile text matching
`в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ`

